WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.160 --> 00:00:03.650
RACHEL AMARA: Hi everyone.

00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:06.880
Welcome to our Artists
at Google today.

00:00:06.880 --> 00:00:08.560
My name is Rachel Amara.

00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:11.920
And I am really excited today to
host and introduce Freddie

00:00:11.920 --> 00:00:14.080
Ravel to everyone.

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:17.480
So my story with Freddie is I
met Freddie a few months ago.

00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:19.940
And he told me about his vision
for helping others

00:00:19.940 --> 00:00:23.600
discover how music relates to
our everyday lives, how it can

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:24.990
help us to tune in--

00:00:24.990 --> 00:00:25.790
no pun intended--

00:00:25.790 --> 00:00:29.900
to live better lives through his
Tune Up concert, which is

00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:32.170
what we're going to
experience today.

00:00:32.170 --> 00:00:36.010
So after that, I knew I had
to bring him to Google.

00:00:36.010 --> 00:00:40.050
Freddie was utterly captivated
by music since age five.

00:00:40.050 --> 00:00:42.990
Freddie has recorded and
performed across six

00:00:42.990 --> 00:00:45.970
continents with luminaries you
may know or heard of like

00:00:45.970 --> 00:00:50.600
Madonna, Prince, the Boston
Pops, Earth, Wind, and Fire,

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:52.980
Carlos Santana, and
many others.

00:00:52.980 --> 00:00:55.520
He's scored numerous Grammys as
well as the coveted number

00:00:55.520 --> 00:00:57.830
one spot in US charts.

00:00:57.830 --> 00:01:00.290
In response to the
ever-increasing challenges to

00:01:00.290 --> 00:01:03.540
effective communication in the
workplace, Freddie created

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:08.040
Tune Up to Success, a unique
peak performance methodology

00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:10.530
based on the universal language
of music that we all

00:01:10.530 --> 00:01:11.630
know and love.

00:01:11.630 --> 00:01:13.980
Dubbed the "Motivational
Maestro" by the city of Los

00:01:13.980 --> 00:01:16.760
Angeles, he continues to garner
acclaim for clients

00:01:16.760 --> 00:01:19.720
such as Google, Apple,
Citi, and NASA.

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:22.810
Today Freddie will share with
us his musical tools for

00:01:22.810 --> 00:01:24.790
creating success in
our personal and

00:01:24.790 --> 00:01:26.350
professional pursuits.

00:01:26.350 --> 00:01:28.560
So please put your hands
together and help me welcome

00:01:28.560 --> 00:01:29.810
Freddie Ravel.

00:01:32.488 --> 00:02:14.070
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:15.531
FREDDIE RAVEL: Put your hands
together, everybody!

00:02:21.722 --> 00:02:24.674
Good afternoon, Google!

00:02:24.674 --> 00:02:26.150
All right!

00:02:26.150 --> 00:02:27.400
Here we go!

00:03:30.322 --> 00:03:34.310
[APPLAUSE]

00:03:34.310 --> 00:03:35.900
FREDDIE RAVEL: Thank
you very much.

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:37.150
[SAYS "THANK YOU" IN MULTIPLE
FOREIGN LANGUAGES]

00:03:50.490 --> 00:03:52.880
I say "thank you," ladies and
gentlemen, in all these

00:03:52.880 --> 00:03:55.820
languages, because we live
in a world of global

00:03:55.820 --> 00:03:59.180
opportunities and challenges.

00:03:59.180 --> 00:04:02.510
Especially in this new digital
universe that we find

00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:04.400
ourselves in.

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:07.870
It's racing before us, where
multiple cutting-edge

00:04:07.870 --> 00:04:11.800
technologies are unfolding as
I say these very words--

00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:15.520
especially in this building.

00:04:15.520 --> 00:04:18.399
And I've got a few questions.

00:04:18.399 --> 00:04:23.620
Is something as fundamental as
email a fabulous thing, or

00:04:23.620 --> 00:04:27.690
this massive thing that eats
away, it saps away of our

00:04:27.690 --> 00:04:30.890
time, the most commodity
that we have?

00:04:30.890 --> 00:04:36.190
Is something like harnessing the
power of Google Hangouts,

00:04:36.190 --> 00:04:40.740
LinkedIn, Facebook, Twitter,
texting-- to enhance our

00:04:40.740 --> 00:04:44.090
personal and professional
relationships--

00:04:44.090 --> 00:04:46.350
is there a better
tool to do that?

00:04:46.350 --> 00:04:50.550
And finally, how do we access
the power and potential of our

00:04:50.550 --> 00:04:54.030
world's greatest asset,
the people?

00:04:54.030 --> 00:04:56.360
The people that we work with,
the people that we play with,

00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:59.940
our clients, and
our colleagues.

00:04:59.940 --> 00:05:05.360
With all this endless data,
what's the next tool that

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:08.620
could help us connect the
information to the people that

00:05:08.620 --> 00:05:11.140
need to use it?

00:05:11.140 --> 00:05:19.170
Today I am delighted to show you
how the structure of music

00:05:19.170 --> 00:05:22.170
is really the structure of
success, and how it provides a

00:05:22.170 --> 00:05:27.440
roadmap for all our pursuits,
personally and professionally.

00:05:27.440 --> 00:05:28.870
How?

00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:32.840
Well the structure of music is
the structure of success.

00:05:32.840 --> 00:05:36.240
Now some of you might be
thinking, how could my

00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:41.740
favorite song have anything
to do with success?

00:05:41.740 --> 00:05:45.080
Well let's take a look.

00:05:45.080 --> 00:05:48.540
Every fantastic piece of music
begins and is built on four

00:05:48.540 --> 00:05:50.030
foundations of music.

00:05:50.030 --> 00:05:52.640
The first foundation
is melody.

00:05:52.640 --> 00:05:55.340
Throughout the ages, we find
that music that soothes the

00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:58.960
soul and survives the centuries
always features a

00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:00.660
strong melody.

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:04.620
Melody is then supported
by harmony.

00:06:04.620 --> 00:06:06.710
Harmony provides the backdrop
that makes the

00:06:06.710 --> 00:06:08.890
melody stand out.

00:06:08.890 --> 00:06:11.310
And then after you have melody
and harmony, you need the

00:06:11.310 --> 00:06:15.480
power of rhythm to drive melody
and harmony forward,

00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:16.840
hence we have rhythm.

00:06:16.840 --> 00:06:20.580
When melody, harmony, and rhythm
all come together, they

00:06:20.580 --> 00:06:24.620
result in what we call
in music the score.

00:06:24.620 --> 00:06:28.145
The score is the totality of
melody, harmony, and rhythm

00:06:28.145 --> 00:06:29.463
coming together.

00:06:29.463 --> 00:06:35.310
Now let's flip over and look
at any business, all right?

00:06:35.310 --> 00:06:37.300
At the beginning of a business,
the very first thing

00:06:37.300 --> 00:06:41.130
that launches all business
is leadership--

00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:43.020
the leader.

00:06:43.020 --> 00:06:48.660
Leadership needs the
power of teamwork.

00:06:48.660 --> 00:06:53.000
After teamwork, you need to be
able to manage this across the

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:54.170
power of time.

00:06:54.170 --> 00:06:57.310
So the management
of time is the

00:06:57.310 --> 00:06:59.320
rhythm that drives business.

00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:03.280
Finally when leadership,
teamwork, and time all come

00:07:03.280 --> 00:07:08.540
together, you arrive at
the score of success.

00:07:08.540 --> 00:07:16.060
So the structure of music is
the structure of success.

00:07:16.060 --> 00:07:17.830
And there's a very organic
reason for

00:07:17.830 --> 00:07:19.450
this, ladies and gentlemen.

00:07:19.450 --> 00:07:23.960
You see, music is with us from
the cradle to the grave.

00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:25.990
I mean you know, we all
enter the world.

00:07:25.990 --> 00:07:28.158
And the first thing
we hear, you know?

00:07:28.158 --> 00:07:29.652
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:29.652 --> 00:07:36.660
FREDDIE RAVEL: And then you
