00:30:45.570 --> 00:30:46.890
that there is no email.

00:30:46.890 --> 00:30:48.700
That there's actually
a conversation.

00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:50.460
And they found out that that
actually increases their

00:30:50.460 --> 00:30:53.000
productivity by having
this policy.

00:30:53.000 --> 00:30:55.560
People actually interface
with each other.

00:30:55.560 --> 00:30:57.870
I might add that Deloitte
&amp; Touche also has

00:30:57.870 --> 00:30:58.840
followed this policy.

00:30:58.840 --> 00:31:02.000
And many other companies are
jumping on, on the bandwagon.

00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:04.510
And it's all about rhythm
and keeping

00:31:04.510 --> 00:31:07.490
time at its most efficient.

00:31:07.490 --> 00:31:12.420
The great Duke Ellington had a
piece of music that was all

00:31:12.420 --> 00:31:14.750
about rhythm.

00:31:14.750 --> 00:31:16.350
He wrote a melody that
