00:32:04.020 --> 00:32:04.890
No rhythm.

00:32:04.890 --> 00:32:06.770
No rhythm whatsoever.

00:32:06.770 --> 00:32:10.000
In fact, Duke Ellington gave
this song a title about the

00:32:10.000 --> 00:32:14.090
consequences of what happens
when melody and harmony run

00:32:14.090 --> 00:32:16.090
awry and there's no rhythm.

00:32:16.090 --> 00:32:20.090
Can anyone tell me the name
of this song, anybody?

00:32:20.090 --> 00:32:20.955
Go ahead, say it.

00:32:20.955 --> 00:32:22.735
AUDIENCE: "It Don't Mean a Thing
(If It Ain't Got That

00:32:22.735 --> 00:32:23.630
Swing)."

00:32:23.630 --> 00:32:25.280
FREDDIE RAVEL: "It Don't Mean a
Thing (If it Ain't Got that

00:32:25.280 --> 00:32:26.230
Swing)." Thank you.

00:32:26.230 --> 00:32:29.570
It don't mean a thing if
we're not listening.

00:32:29.570 --> 00:32:32.405
You can have empowered
individuals, leaders, who sing

00:32:32.405 --> 00:32:33.840
a great melody.

00:32:33.840 --> 00:32:35.960
You could have a fantastic
team supporting them.

00:32:35.960 --> 00:32:39.260
But until they become in sync
with the game plan of time

00:32:39.260 --> 00:32:43.630
management and their rhythm is
paced across time, it don't

00:32:43.630 --> 00:32:44.280
mean a thing.

00:32:44.280 --> 00:32:46.570
But when they come together and
march to the beat of the

00:32:46.570 --> 00:32:47.580
same drummer, you get--

00:32:47.580 --> 00:33:11.750
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:33:11.750 --> 00:33:14.180
FREDDIE RAVEL: Don't mean a
thing, if it ain't go that

00:33:14.180 --> 00:33:20.690
swing, do wop, do wop, do wop,
as Duke Ellington would say.

00:33:20.690 --> 00:33:23.580
The structure of music is the
structure of success.

00:33:23.580 --> 00:33:26.650
You can look at it from so many
different angles, but

00:33:26.650 --> 00:33:28.650
it's always there.

00:33:28.650 --> 00:33:31.760
We discussed the power
of listening.

00:33:31.760 --> 00:33:34.290
Then we went to the
power of melody.

00:33:34.290 --> 00:33:37.500
Then we went to the power of
collaboration with purpose, of

00:33:37.500 --> 00:33:39.830
harmony, and discussed
the management

00:33:39.830 --> 00:33:42.720
of time over rhythm.

00:33:42.720 --> 00:33:47.480
This seems simple on
many levels, right?

00:33:47.480 --> 00:33:51.580
But like everything in
life, there is a

00:33:51.580 --> 00:33:54.630
villain that shows up.

00:33:54.630 --> 00:33:56.290
It's called you know,
dissonance.

00:33:56.290 --> 00:33:59.390
It's that moment where
I've got an idea.

00:33:59.390 --> 00:34:00.350
And she's got an idea.

00:34:00.350 --> 00:34:02.550
And then someone else
has an idea.

00:34:02.550 --> 00:34:07.903
No one returns the call and no
one's responding to this one.

00:34:07.903 --> 00:34:09.795
And they're about to
nix this idea.

00:34:09.795 --> 00:34:10.741
And I'm really not sure.

00:34:10.741 --> 00:34:11.564
And I'm kind of overwhelmed.

00:34:11.564 --> 00:34:12.475
And why is this spam
happening.

00:34:12.475 --> 00:34:15.046
And why did the system
go down.

00:34:15.046 --> 00:34:17.726
And why isn't this working,
people screaming at me.

00:34:17.726 --> 00:34:20.166
Dissonance!

00:34:20.166 --> 00:34:25.130
A reality for every human
being on planet Earth.

00:34:25.130 --> 00:34:29.159
But music has a very powerful
way of dealing with

00:34:29.159 --> 00:34:31.260
dissonance.

00:34:31.260 --> 00:34:35.710
Dissonance is actually conflict
and opportunity at

00:34:35.710 --> 00:34:37.570
the same time.

00:34:37.570 --> 00:34:42.130
And if we manage it the right
way, dissonance makes music

00:34:42.130 --> 00:34:45.290
going from the bland
to the grand.

00:34:45.290 --> 00:34:47.850
It takes something that's very
vanilla sounding and actually

00:34:47.850 --> 00:34:50.120
makes it astounding.

00:34:50.120 --> 00:34:51.670
And this is what happens.

00:34:51.670 --> 00:34:56.949
Especially when we learn
to agree to disagree.

00:34:56.949 --> 00:34:58.500
This is one of the key things.

00:34:58.500 --> 00:35:00.650
And I want to share with you
a quick story about two

00:35:00.650 --> 00:35:04.480
songwriters that you may be
familiar with, John Lennon and

00:35:04.480 --> 00:35:06.330
Paul McCartney.

00:35:06.330 --> 00:35:10.480
And John Lennon and Paul
McCartney statistically, over

00:35:10.480 --> 00:35:14.420
the years, rank as the most
successful songwriting team in

00:35:14.420 --> 00:35:15.210
the history of music.

00:35:15.210 --> 00:35:18.280
Their music has been around
for 50 years now,

00:35:18.280 --> 00:35:20.630
and it still is vital.

00:35:20.630 --> 00:35:23.460
And one thing that made that
particular group exceptionally

00:35:23.460 --> 00:35:27.760
dynamic is that they
agreed to disagree.

00:35:27.760 --> 00:35:33.670
Paul McCartney wrote the
optimistic, sunny side of many

00:35:33.670 --> 00:35:34.690
of the Beatles songs.

00:35:34.690 --> 00:35:38.300
Whereas John Lennon would
write the more dark,

00:35:38.300 --> 00:35:41.250
melancholy perspective
on the music.

00:35:41.250 --> 00:35:43.630
So if we take a song, for
example, like "We Can Work It

00:35:43.630 --> 00:35:45.960
Out," by the Beatles, right,
by John Lennon and Paul

00:35:45.960 --> 00:35:50.560
McCartney, Paul comes in with
this very optimistic idea.

00:35:50.560 --> 00:36:02.070
[SINGING]

00:36:02.070 --> 00:36:02.900
Full of optimism.

00:36:02.900 --> 00:36:04.390
We can work it out.

00:36:04.390 --> 00:36:07.600
I mean the sun shining
when he sings this.

00:36:07.600 --> 00:36:09.440
In the same song--

00:36:09.440 --> 00:36:12.070
in the very same piece of
music-- and very few pieces of

00:36:12.070 --> 00:36:13.940
music ever do this--

00:36:13.940 --> 00:36:17.990
John Lennon comes in, not in a
major chord, he comes in on a

00:36:17.990 --> 00:36:18.970
minor chord.

00:36:18.970 --> 00:36:21.250
Not in the same rhythm
that Paul just said--

00:36:21.250 --> 00:36:23.690
in a completely different
rhythm and a completely

00:36:23.690 --> 00:36:24.450
different message.

00:36:24.450 --> 00:36:25.795
He says [SINGING].

00:36:34.490 --> 00:36:36.300
Completely different.

00:36:36.300 --> 00:36:37.830
The Beatles understood this.

00:36:37.830 --> 00:36:41.660
And this is why their music is
timeless in so many ways.

00:36:41.660 --> 00:36:44.960
It continues to live on because
they understood how to

00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:47.780
agree to disagree.

00:36:47.780 --> 00:36:50.155
Conflict resolution
at its best.

00:36:54.770 --> 00:36:58.040
So my friends here at Google,
I got to tell you, we don't

00:36:58.040 --> 00:37:01.240
just carry music in an iPod.

00:37:01.240 --> 00:37:04.340
We carry music in our hearts.

00:37:04.340 --> 00:37:09.060
Food, water, shelter, music.

00:37:09.060 --> 00:37:13.390
Music is a core survival tool.

00:37:13.390 --> 00:37:16.960
The six-year-old kid in Rio de
Janeiro who picks up a gas can

00:37:16.960 --> 00:37:20.450
and a stick and starts drumming
on that to relieve

00:37:20.450 --> 00:37:23.800
the pangs of hunger he feels
in this stomach.

00:37:23.800 --> 00:37:27.800
The college student who enrolls
in an after-school

00:37:27.800 --> 00:37:31.630
music program and because of
that has a shot of increasing

00:37:31.630 --> 00:37:36.200
her test scores by a national
average of 20% because she

00:37:36.200 --> 00:37:38.380
studies music.

00:37:38.380 --> 00:37:43.990
Or a Congresswoman by the name
of Gabby Giffords who

00:37:43.990 --> 00:37:48.540
attributes her amazing
miraculous recovery from a

00:37:48.540 --> 00:37:53.765
gunshot to the head to
the power of music.

00:37:56.420 --> 00:38:00.430
We are dealing with the rocket
fuel for humanity.

00:38:00.430 --> 00:38:03.270
This is what music truly is.

00:38:03.270 --> 00:38:07.130
And we have landed on the fourth
foundation of music,

00:38:07.130 --> 00:38:10.030
which is called the score.

00:38:10.030 --> 00:38:11.610
Melody--

00:38:11.610 --> 00:38:13.360
to help us express leadership.

00:38:13.360 --> 00:38:16.110
Harmony to express collaboration
and teamwork.

00:38:16.110 --> 00:38:19.210
Rhythm to pace us across time.

00:38:19.210 --> 00:38:23.710
And the score where we achieve
our dreams of success.

00:38:23.710 --> 00:38:27.740
The structure of music is the
structure of success.

