00:45:46.860 --> 00:45:51.030
There are four particular points
that I've been driving

00:45:51.030 --> 00:45:52.110
home through the talk.

00:45:52.110 --> 00:45:54.800
The structure of music is the
structure of success.

00:45:54.800 --> 00:45:57.820
And that melody is
a lead idea.

00:45:57.820 --> 00:46:00.570
And harmony is a collaborative
idea.

00:46:00.570 --> 00:46:03.980
And rhythm is an idea
about time.

00:46:03.980 --> 00:46:06.800
And the score is the holistic
sum of that,

00:46:06.800 --> 00:46:08.150
the sum of that total.

00:46:08.150 --> 00:46:11.620
Sometimes when you can look
at something as complex as

00:46:11.620 --> 00:46:16.220
teamwork or as complex as human
interfaces, right, and

00:46:16.220 --> 00:46:20.080
drill it down to the way the
basic structure of music is,

00:46:20.080 --> 00:46:22.060
it can be very beneficial.

00:46:22.060 --> 00:46:25.460
For example you're working with
a team person and they

00:46:25.460 --> 00:46:27.440
really are in a different key.

00:46:27.440 --> 00:46:28.820
I mean they're in a completely
different key.

00:46:28.820 --> 00:46:31.890
And it really sounds like
that example I gave you.

00:46:31.890 --> 00:46:36.310
You may look at it and instead
of getting completely upset at

00:46:36.310 --> 00:46:39.090
the dissonance that you're
having with that team member,

00:46:39.090 --> 00:46:42.250
you might step back and
say wait a second.

00:46:42.250 --> 00:46:44.400
That person's really coming
from almost a completely

00:46:44.400 --> 00:46:46.790
different culture, a different
perspective.

00:46:46.790 --> 00:46:49.690
They are in a different key.

00:46:49.690 --> 00:46:53.540
So what can I do to
adapt to that key?

00:46:53.540 --> 00:46:56.950
So this may be a message in this
context about adapting

00:46:56.950 --> 00:47:01.140
and conforming, finding that
agree to disagree.

00:47:01.140 --> 00:47:04.710
Because the only way we grow,
the only way any company

00:47:04.710 --> 00:47:07.760
